definition: Gaotai county in Zhangye 張掖|张掖[Zhang1 ye4], Gansu
Gaotai county in Zhangye 張掖|张掖[Zhang1 ye4], Gansu

sentences.english: Holiday travel market cooling, domestic air fares in advance "high platform diving."
sentences.chinese: 假期旅游市场降温，国内机票价格提前“高台跳水”。

sentences.english: Tell me why it's called Miaogaotai?
sentences.chinese: 那你说它为什么会叫妙高台呢？

sentences.english: The movements they make in the air are very similar to what you might see from top divers .
sentences.chinese: 他们在空中做的动作跟我们看到的高台跳水很相似。

sentences.english: A boy at a swimming pool climbed up to the high diving board.
sentences.chinese: 一个男孩爬上游泳池的高台跳水板。

sentences.english: The diver dived into the pool from the high diving board.
sentences.chinese: 跳水运动员从高台跳板上一头扎进水池里。

sentences.english: A man and his camel walk past a solar eclipse in Gaotai, Gansu province in China.
sentences.chinese: 在甘肃高台，一名男子牵着骆驼走在日食的光晕下。

sentences.english: But diving from a high platform is more adventurous, more exciting.
sentences.chinese: 但是高台跳水更冒险更刺激。

sentences.english: Duke Gong of Chu stood on a high platform built on chariot and watched the movements of the Jin army.
sentences.chinese: 楚共王站在架有高台的战车上观察晋军的动静。

sentences.english: The platform helps keep the house well above flood levels.
sentences.chinese: 这个高台帮助这幢房屋保持在洪水水面之上。

sentences.english: The diver poised on the edge of the high board.
sentences.chinese: 跳水者在高台边上站稳。

sentences.english: He leaped on to the platform with a thump.
sentences.chinese: 跳水者在高台边上站稳。

sentences.english: That thou hast also built unto thee an eminent place, and hast made thee an high place in every street.
sentences.chinese: 又为自己建造圆顶花楼，在各街上作了高台。

sentences.english: She dived in off the high board.
